# Taifho 2025 Project Guidelines

## Language

- Code: English (variables, functions, comments)
- Git commits: English
- Documentation: English

## Code Style

- Use 2 spaces for indentation
- Use single quotes for strings
- No semicolons (unless required)
- Use arrow functions for callbacks
- Use `const` by default, `let` when needed, never `var`

## File Naming

- Components: `PascalCase.tsx`
- Utilities/logic: `camelCase.ts`
- Types: `camelCase.ts` or group in `types.ts`
- Tests: `*.test.ts` or `*.test.tsx`
- CSS: `ComponentName.css` (matching component)

## Git Commits

Format: `type: short description`

Types:
- `feat:` - New feature
- `fix:` - Bug fix
- `refactor:` - Code restructuring
- `docs:` - Documentation
- `test:` - Tests
- `chore:` - Maintenance

## Before Completing Work

1. ✅ No TypeScript errors (`npm run build`)
2. ✅ Tests pass (`npm test`)
3. ✅ Linting passes (`npm run lint`)
4. ✅ Code is formatted consistently
5. ✅ New code has appropriate tests
6. ✅ Documentation updated if needed

## Dependencies

- Don't add new dependencies without good reason
- Prefer built-in/existing solutions
- If adding dependency, document why in commit message

## Performance

- Don't optimize prematurely
- Profile before optimizing
- Document any intentional performance trade-offs
